main event: A report of unidentified flying objects observed in Los Angeles on May 28, 1964.
interesting points: The sighting was categorized with multiple possible explanations including balloon, aircraft, or searchlights reflecting off fog., Three objects were reported during the observation., The report stated that the duration of the sighting and details about changes in lights were omitted., Fog was noted as a significant factor in the visibility of the objects., The report was part of the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book, which investigated UFO sightings.
witness description: Details about witnesses are not specified in the report.
